name: Realms of Arkania: Blade of Destiny + Star Trail
Grid Run and Pontoon
description:
Grid Run and Pontoon is a compilation featuring two distinct games:

Grid Run is an action-packed maze game reminiscent of classic arcade titles. Players navigate a simple grid, collecting dots while avoiding computer-controlled cars. The unique control scheme uses just two keys to shift lanes inward or outward, creating a challenging and fast-paced experience. With automatic movement and a focus on quick decision-making, Grid Run offers an addictive, high-score-chasing gameplay loop. Bonus cars are awarded every 10,000 points, adding to the game's replay value.

Pontoon offers a digital version of the popular card game, also known as Blackjack. Players aim to build a hand as close to 21 as possible without going over, competing against a computer dealer. The game features logical ace play by the computer and provides comprehensive on-screen result assessments, making it accessible for both newcomers and experienced players.

name: Söldner: Marine Corps
description:
Marine Corps is an add-on for the multiplayer warfare game Söldner: Secret Wars. Marine Corps' most prominent feature is the inclusion of combat on water. The expansion adds ships and vessels such as jet skis, patrol boats and amphibious vehicles. There are ten new maps in total with both island and desert scenarios. Various new weapons (including laser-steered rockets), vehicles, tanks (Leopard, Mungo...) and planes such as the Tornado and the Eurofighter are now available. Next to general improvements to the interface and COMM mode, certain weaknesses and strengths have been rebalanced.

Owners of the base game or the re-release Söldner: Secret Wars - Reloaded can still go into battle with players with the add-on, even if they don't own it themselves, if they apply patch 33588 that was provided prior to the release. All the new features of the expansion are then available, but the new weapons, vehicles and vessels are not accessible. However, if a player with the expansion drops a new weapon or leaves a new vehicle, it can be used by all players.

The game was co-developed by what was left of Wings Simulations, after JoWood had announced to close the studio, and a new development team: Project-Z development.

name: Mankind
description:
Discover with MANKIND the finest elements of galactic strategy exclusively online. Be one of an infinite number of possible players in a universe where many are already immersed in battle and many more will join the ever-expanding game environment. 
 
In order to succeed, you will have to bring to your empire your strategic knowledge and tactical abilities by committing your life to the cause. Colonize your planets, develop your spatial and ground infrastructures, and manage your resources to Ensure the survival of your colonies whilst forging alliances with other members of your faction to protect your system.

name: Sadness
description: Sadness was a survival horror video game in development by Nibris for the Wii console and was one of the earliest titles announced for the system. While the game initially drew positive attention for its unique gameplay concepts, such as black-and-white graphics and emphasis on psychological horror over violence, Sadness became notorious when no evidence of a playable build was ever publicly released during the four years it spent in development. It was revealed that Sadness had entered development hell due to problems with deadlines and relationships with external developers, leading to its eventual cancellation by 2010, along with the permanent closure of the company.

name: The Entrepreneur
description: Become The Entrepreneur they need! In this choice-driven adventure, you will dive into a world filled with fun, drama, high stakes, sex, and much more. Build relationships, face immense challenges, and feel the consequences of your decisions affecting those around you! What lies ahead for you?

name: TimeO
description: TimeO was the last game developed by ZootFly before its closure. The project was never completed, starting life as a concept for a Ghostbusters game, The game was described as "a daring and upbeat action adventure about two diehard New York City urban explorers. They discover an entrance to a parallel world in which an army of enslaved people is building replicas of cities in order to launch a Trojan horse invasion on Earth and other worlds."

name: Ushiro
description:
Ushiro is a turn-based RPG which features a young protagonist interacting with ghosts in real-world Japanese locations, such as Tokyo's Shibuya district. Despite receiving write ups, trailers and gameplay footage, the supposed PSP title never saw the light of day.

However, according to Famitsu's interview with Level 5 President Akihiro Hino, Ushiro is back on the books and will be coming to Nintendo Switch instead, although Hino does go on to admit that development is still in its very early stages.
